# Ikura

Ikura is a credit card debt payment plan website. Users enter in three numbers per card (credit card debt, apr, and how long they want to pay off their debts). Ikura uses this information to calculate how much money a user would need to pay off their debts within their specified time frame. 

Ikura also serves to educate the user on the perils of paying only the minimum payment that credit cards suggest. 

